title: The Mourning court, or, The Solemn representation of the royal funeral of that most illustrious Princess Mar[y], late Queen of England, Scotland, France, and Ireland, &c. who changed this earthly crown for a more glorious and celestial diadem on the 28th of December, 1694, and was interred in King Hen[ry's] chappel at Westminster, on the 5th of March 1695 ...
